entries.name: ZkToken
entries.description: The ZK token contract on ZKsync Era. Mintable through access control roles. Used for voting in the ZK stack governance system.

receivedPermissions.description: cancel proposals while they are pending (after having been proposed) or active (during the voting period).
cancel proposals while they are pending (after having been proposed) or active (during the voting period).

entries.name: ZkProtocolGovernor
entries.description: Main Governance contract allowing for token voting (simple majority) with the ZK token through delegates. This contract is used for protocol upgrade proposals (ZIPs) that start on ZKsync Era, go through Ethereum Layer 1 and can - from there - target all L1 and L2 contracts. At least 21M ZK tokens are necessary to start a proposal and a 630M quorum of voted tokens must be met to succeed.

receivedPermissions.description: manage all access control roles and change the minimum delay.

entries.name: ZkTokenGovernor
entries.description: Governance contract allowing for token voting (simple majority) with the ZK token through delegates. This contract is used for Token Program Proposals (TPPs) usually targeting the ZK token on ZKsync Era. At least 21M ZK tokens are necessary to start a proposal (for delegates) and a 630M quorum of voted tokens must be met to succeed.

receivedPermissions.description: grant the MINTER_ROLE to arbitrary addresses, thus controlling the minting of the ZK token.
manage all access control roles and change the minimum delay.

entries.name: GovOpsTimelockController

directlyReceivedPermissions.description: manage all access control roles and change the minimum delay.

receivedPermissions.description: make direct proposals without owning ZK tokens. In propose-guarded mode, this address is the ONLY allowed proposer. Propose-guarded mode is currently set to false.

entries.name: ZkGovOpsGovernor
entries.description: Governance contract allowing for token voting (simple majority) with the ZK token through delegates. This contract is used for Governance Advisory Proposals (GAPs) that are not executable onchain. At least 21M ZK tokens are necessary to start a proposal and a 630M quorum of voted tokens must be met to succeed.

receivedPermissions.description: manage all access control roles and change the minimum delay.
control all roles in the ZkToken access control, including the minter roles.
